+**Path-segment scoping makes order non-load-bearing.** FastAPI /
+Starlette path parameters default to single-segment matching:
+`{experiment_id}` matches one path segment with no slashes. So
+`GET /v0/experiments/{experiment_id}` matches **only**
+`/v0/experiments/<id>` — it does **not** shadow
+`/v0/experiments/<id>/tasks` or any other sub-resource. Every
+existing route has a unique fully-qualified path; there is no
+ordering-dependent matching today.
