+### 3.7 Per-route auth matrix
+
+The current `make_app` uses a mix of: (a) the four shared
+helpers (`_enforce_worker`, `_enforce_in_any_group`,
+`_stamp_created_by`, `_check_experiment`); (b) direct calls to
+`require_admin(request)` / `require_worker(request)` /
+`authenticate(...)` from `eden_wire.auth`; (c) inline
+`if admin_token is not None` branches that gate behavior
+on whether auth is installed. The refactor MUST preserve all
+three patterns route-by-route — F-3 is not an opportunity to
+unify the auth surface (that would be a behavior change).
+
+Authoritative matrix per route. "Helper" = uses `enforce_*` /
+`require_*` from `_dependencies.py`. "Direct" = imports
+`require_admin` / `require_worker` / `authenticate` from
+`eden_wire.auth` and calls it directly. "Either-auth" = guarded
+by `if admin_token is not None: _ = request.state.principal`
+(any registered worker passes). "None-fallthrough" = behavior
+when `admin_token is None` (test posture).
+
