+**Refactor invariants from this matrix.**
+
+1. **Direct callers stay direct.** `routers/workers.py`,
+   `routers/groups.py`, `routers/checkpoints.py`,
+   `routers/reference.py` import `require_admin` /
+   `require_worker` / `authenticate` from `eden_wire.auth` and
+   call them directly with the same `if deps.admin_token is not
+   None` branches as today. They do NOT route through the four
+   helpers in `_dependencies.py`.
+2. **Either-auth stays inline.** The four either-auth sites
+   (`GET /dispatch_mode`, `GET /state`, `GET /v0/experiments/{id}`,
+   `GET /workers`) keep the inline `if deps.admin_token is not
+   None: _ = request.state.principal` check. The plan does NOT
+   introduce an `enforce_either` helper — adding one is feature-
+   creep beyond F-3's scope.
+3. **`_worker_id_from_request` semantics preserved.** The helper
+   stays at module scope in `_dependencies.py`; both the test-mode
+   `X-Eden-Worker-Id` header fallback AND the `"anonymous"`
+   sentinel are preserved.
+4. **The `whoami` route is the only direct `require_worker`
+   call.** All other worker-gated routes go through
+   `enforce_worker`. Don't unify.
+5. **`POST /tasks`'s split-by-kind authority** (lines 631–637)
+   stays inline in the tasks router — moving the per-kind branch
+   into `enforce_in_any_group` would over-specialize the helper.
+6. **`POST /workers` + `POST /groups` pass `registered_by =
+   principal.kind` / `created_by = principal.kind`** when
+   `admin_token is not None`, else `None`. This is a §13.1
+   attribution detail; preserve verbatim in each router.
+
